// `/v2/accounts/{aid}/members` or `/v2/users/{id}`.
//
// This is now extended with `kind` + `display_name` captured at
// write time:
//
//   - `kind = "user"`      — id is the user.id; display_name is
//     "First Last" or email fallback.
//   - `kind = "api_token"` — id is the api_token.id (NOT the
//     owning user); display_name is the
//     token's friendly name (e.g.
//     "ci-bot-prod"). Distinguishes
//     token-driven calls from web-console
//     calls by the same person.
//   - `kind = "system"`    — id is the cron / job slug.
